{"cursor":"4415","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox writer \n| name = Janey Morris King image = image_size = alt = caption = pseudonym =\n| Rosie Thomas birth_name = Janey Morris birth_date = birth_place = Denbigh,\n| Wales, UK death_date =  death_place = resting_place = occupation =\n| Novelist language = English nationality = British ethnicity = citizenship =\n| education = journalist, novelist alma_mater = period = 1982âpresent genre =\n| Romance subject = movement = notableworks = spouse = partner = children =\n| relatives = influences = influenced = awards = signature = signature_alt =\n| website = portaldisp =\n}}\n\n'Janey King' (nÃ©e Morris; born 1947) is British journalist and writer of romance\nnovels; she writes under the pseudonym of 'Rosie Thomas'. She was educated at Millfield and later studied at St\nHilda's College, Oxford. She worked as a journalist and in publishing before\nwriting full time. She is one of only a few authors to have\nwon twice the Romantic Novel of the Year Award by the Romantic Novelists'\nAssociation.\n\n\nShe has published numerous novels since 1982,with several of them becoming top\nten bestsellers; her books deal with the common themes of love and loss. {{cite web|last=|first=|title= Rosie Thomas|url=http://www.harpercollins.co.uk/Authors/6539/rosie-\nthomas|work=Harper Collins website|date=|accessdate=2010-02-09}} She won\nthe Romantic Novel of the Year Award by her novel Sunrise in 1985 and in 2007 by\nher novel Iris and Ruby.\n\nShe is a keen traveller and mountaineer. {{cite\nweb|last=Wilkinson|first=Carl|title= Me and my travels: Rosie Thomas,\nauthor|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/travel/2008/apr/06/10|work=The Guardian|date=2008-04-06|accessdate=2010-02-\n09}} and has competed in the Peking to Paris car rally. She lives in London.\n","linknr":144,"url":"Rosie_Thomas_(writer)","recorded":1375080511,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Rosie_Thomas_(writer)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Rosie_Thomas_